  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF EVASIVE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;52</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;3 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;15 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;7 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>The warrior is hit by his opponent less often but also will hit his target less often.  This discipline lasts for 3 minutes and has a base reuse time of 15 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>RESPONDING TO BRYARR</span><b>, By Popedo</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Disciplines are not that way. If at 60 this has a refresh time of 7 minutes and lasts for three minutes, the 7 minutes start ticking as soon as you enable the discipline. In essence, there is a 4 minute reuse time.<P> 

That said, I don't see why anyone would use this discipline at 60. It is by far the least useful. At 55 a warrior gets Defensive, which lasts the same amount of time, has the same amount of base reuse time, and works about 50% better.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>52 CHAMPION LUCLIN</span><b>, By Marcellus wallace</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I've been using this skill extensively in Old Sebilis. Sebilite Juggernauts like to Rampage when low on life, and tend to do silly amounts of damage. Hit Evasive and it's not nearly as bad as it could be.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>LESS DAMAGE = LESS TAUNT FACTOR?</span><b>, By Strohm</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>My question is this,  if you are dealing less damage then wouldn't it stand to reason that your taunt factor might be lessened as well.  Not trying to say that the Taunt ability or Skill would be lessened but it is a proven fact that the amount of damage being dealt to a mob by a PC during a certain period of time has a correlation to the amount of taunt factor that PC has to that mob. I would think this might cause a problem in some situations.  Such as when a wizard is blasting away at a mob and it aggros on him.  The warrior might have less of a chance to pull it off.  Sounds like the main use of this Discipline would be getting away from trains.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WARRIOR OF TUNARE</span><b>, By Elite</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Well the skill does infact work, as to the percentiles..I am uncertain. All I know is when I use it, its pretty good. My team usually consits of myself and a shaman. Problem at that time is, I am not a meat shield but a DOT. When I hit evasive it means we need to clear the zone.... Tried it in hate, saved me a time or two. Depends on the senario I suppose<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>RECYCLE</span><b>, By Phyrephly5</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>At a recycle time of 7 minutes, you could keep this discipline up 30% of the time.  In my book, 30% is still 20% away from 50%.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
